ğŸ§‘â€ğŸ’» Security Operation Teams
ğŸ”´ Red Team â€“ Attackers
Think of them as ethical hackers.
Their job is to attack systems (legally) just like real cybercriminals would.
Purpose: Find weaknesses before real hackers do.
Example: They try to hack into a companyâ€™s server or steal fake passwords to test defenses.

ğŸ”µ Blue Team â€“ Defenders
They are the security protectors of the organization.
Their job is to detect, stop, and respond to attacks.
Purpose: Protect systems, data, and networks.
Example: They monitor systems, block attacks, and fix security gaps.

ğŸŸ£ Purple Team â€“ Bridge Between Red and Blue
They connect the Red and Blue Teams.
Their job is to help both teams work together and learn from each other.
Purpose: Improve security faster by sharing attack and defense knowledge.
Example: After an attack simulation, they analyze what happened and help fix weak points.

