ğŸª Session ID & Cookies (Clear Explanation)

When you login to a website, the server needs a way to remember you as you move from one page to another.
This is done using sessions and cookies.

ğŸ” What is a Session?

A session is a temporary storage on the server that keeps user information after login.

Example session data stored on the server:

Key	Value
session_id	abc123xyz
user_id	101
name	Moses
role	user

The session data stays on the server â€” safe and private.

ğŸª What is a Cookie?

A cookie is a small piece of text stored in your browser.

After login:

The server creates a session.

The server generates a unique Session ID.

The server stores the Session ID + user details on the server.

The server sends ONLY the Session ID back to your browser as a cookie.
